                                <p align="justify">
                                	<font color="#333333" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="font-size:12px;">
                                		With the equity  markets registering a weak performance over the last few months, investor  sentiment is low and most are looking to exit the market. During such periods  investors prefer to switch from equity instruments to debt based options which  attract comparatively lower risk. Some investors also prefer to opt for fixed  income based options like fixed deposits.
                                	</font>
                                </p>
                                
                                <p align="justify">
                                	<font color="#333333" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="font-size:12px;">
                                		However, while the tendency during this point is to exit the equity market, we would advise you to remain invested in the equity markets. We tell you why…  
                                	</font></p>
	                                <ul>
	                                  <li>
	                                    	<div align="justify">
	                                    		<font color="#333333" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="font-size:12px;" align="justify">
	                                    			<strong>Base it on your financial plan</strong><br />
	                                      			Most of the investments that we advise our clients to make are based on a financial plan with specific goals. Hence, when one is working towards attaining the financial goal, the focus should continue to remain on the long term plan rather than short term changes.
	                                      		</font><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;
	                                      	</div>
	                                  </li>
	                                  <li>
	                                    	<div align="justify">
	                                    		<font color="#333333" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="font-size:12px;" align="justify"> 
	                                    			<strong>Good time to enter the market</strong><br />
	                                      			The current valuations of equity stocks make them an attractive proposition. Since many stocks are trading at a discount, one can enter the market at a lower rate. While some may be concerned about the markets moving further southwards, it is difficult to time the markets. Hence, it is time in the market which is more important than timing the market
	                                      		</font><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;
	                                      	</div>
	                                  </li>
	                                  
	                                  <li>
	                                    	<div align="justify">
	                                    		<font color="#333333" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="font-size:12px;" align="justify"> 
	                                    			<strong>Equity only for long term</strong><br />
	                                      			Given the volatility of equity markets, your short term financial goals are unlikely to rely on equity based investments. And from a long term perspective, the outlook towards the equity markets remains positive, helping you get sustained growth. Based on your goal your financial planner assigns asset allocation which helps you gets you get exposure into equity fixed income goals, of which equity as a long term goal.
	                                      		</font>
	                                      	</div>
	                                  </li>
	                                </ul>                                
	                                	<p align="justify">
	                                		<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#333333" style="font-size:12px;">
	                                			Following a disciplined approach, with the help of compounding can gain higher returns when investing for a long term plan. Investing in a disciplined fashion results in a more consistent increase in the total asset value. <br>
	                                			</br><br/> The purpose of a good financial plan is to make sure that irrespective of your goals, it would come true using the right tools and products. And the equity market, on the whole, can help in that direction.
	                                		</font>
	                                	</p>
