                                <p align="justify"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#333333" style="font-size:12px;">
                                	<strong>Way forward &amp; Products to focus on</strong><br /> 
                                  	The banking system is likely to witness pressure on its profitability due to the changes in the credit policy. It is likely that banks will increase both deposit rates as well as lending rates in a gradual manner. Therefore, it makes sense to remain invested in low duration funds at the moment and wait for money market rates to peak out in the next three to six months before seeking to extend the duration of investments.
                                  	</font></p>
                                <p align="justify"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#333333" style="font-size:12px;">
                                	While we may be nearing the end of the tightening cycle for interest rates, it would be advisable to remain away from interest rate sensitive at this juncture.  As a part of your financial plan, the focus should clearly be on short term accrual like strategies provided by liquid plus funds and/or lock in Fixed Maturity Plans (FMP) kind of strategies. FMPs would be a very good option for investors not wanting significant interest rate exposure and at the same time looking for a 1 year investment avenue.
